summary: SEATTLE, November 19, 2025--F5 (NASDAQ: FFIV) today announced the creation of its Application Delivery and Security Platform (ADSP) Partner Program, designed to cultivate a sophisticated ecosystem of technology partners that extend the capabilities of F5’s industry-leading platform. headline: Doppel Raises $70M Series C to Meet Rising Demand for AI-Driven Social Engineering Defense
summary: Doppel, the AI-native social engineering defense (SED) platform, today announced a $70 million Series C funding round, just six months following its Series B. Led by Bessemer Venture Partners, this brings the total amount raised to $124M and the company's valuation to over $600M. headline: Will CrowdStrike’s Latest Big-Tech Alliances Strengthen Its Competitive Edge in AI Security Solutions (CRWD)?
summary: In recent weeks, CrowdStrike announced several major developments, including its selection as an inaugural partner in the Google Unified Security Recommended program, a new technology alliance with F5 to integrate Falcon Sensor with BIG-IP, and a global partnership with CoreWeave to power secure AI cloud foundations. These moves underscore CrowdStrike’s expanding influence in AI-driven cybersecurity, marking its technology as a preferred choice for cloud and critical infrastructure security...
